# Pickable optional packages for `boot pick`.
#
# Adding a package = one line. Pipe-delimited (kept dependency-free so the bash picker needs
# no TOML parser). Columns:
#
#   label | type | name | profiles | default
#
#     label    human name shown in the picker
#     type     cask | brew | nix   (cask/brew -> Homebrew, nix -> nixpkgs attr)
#     name     the Homebrew cask/formula name, or the nixpkgs attribute
#     profiles comma-separated: engineer,staff  (who may pick it)
#     default  on | off  (preselected in the picker)
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.

Spotify            | cask | spotify              | engineer,staff | off
VS Code            | cask | visual-studio-code   | engineer       | off
Docker Desktop     | cask | docker               | engineer       | off
Figma              | cask | figma                | engineer,staff | off
Notion             | cask | notion               | engineer,staff | off
Rectangle          | cask | rectangle            | engineer,staff | on
Zoom               | cask | zoom                 | engineer,staff | on
httpie             | nix  | httpie               | engineer       | off
